    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_16_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_16",
      "description": "Available now is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies. This high-revving power plant delivers 333 hp through a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a factory M-variable differential lock. The vehicle remains mechanically robust with a documented VANOS overhaul and rear subframe reinforcement already completed. While the exterior shows minor stone chips consistent with spirited use, the chassis remains composed with refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers. Inside, the Nappa leather exhibits a light patina, but the seat bolsters remain firm and the instrumentation is fully functional. This is a mechanically sound, well-sorted example of the ultimate driving machine, optimized for the purist who values tactile feedback and linear power delivery.",
